A benchmark measures how fast your code runs.

```
func BenchmarkAdd(b *testing.B) {
    for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
        add(100, 200)
    }
}
```

`b.N` is set automatically by the testing framework — it runs enough iterations to get a stable measurement. Run with `go test -bench=.`

